Based on the cumulative understanding of the provided context, we can move beyond lists and text to a more holistic, visual representation. A technical graph is the perfect way to model the dynamic, interconnected nature of the procedures, considerations, and protocols discussed.

This isn't just a simple flowchart; it's an architectural blueprint for an advanced, self-improving agentic system. It models two primary cycles:

1.  **The Inner Loop (The Agentic Runtime):** The real-time, step-by-step execution of a single task, heavily governed by context management.
2.  **The Outer Loop (The Evolutionary Framework):** The long-term, meta-level processes that improve the system over time without retraining the core model.

Below is the scaffolded technical graph, followed by a detailed breakdown of each component and its function within The New Fuse (TNF) framework.

### **Technical Graph: The New Fuse (TNF) Agentic Orchestration & Evolution Framework**

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph " "
        direction LR
        subgraph "Outer Loop: System Evolution & Evaluation"
            direction TB
            A1(User Feedback<br>1-5 Star Ratings) --> B1{Parameter-Free<br>Online Learning};
            A2(User Corrections<br>In-flight guidance) --> B1;
            A3(Automated Eval Results<br>Verifiable Tests) --> B1;
            B1 --> C1(Aggregate & Cluster<br>Identify Failure Patterns);
            C1 --> D1(Synthesize Wisdom<br>Create Procedural Heuristics);
            D1 -.-> E1[(Wisdom DB<br>RAG for "How-To")];

            F1(Model Scalability Index<br>MSI Calculation) -- "Triggers" --> G1{Architectural<br>Plasticity Protocol};
            G1 -- "Drives" --> H1(Scaffolding<br>Simplification Review);
            H1 -.-> CoreSys[Core TNF Scaffolding];
        end

        subgraph "Inner Loop: Agentic Runtime (Single Task)"
            direction TB
            User_Goal[User Goal] --> Orchestrator{TNF Orchestrator};
            Orchestrator -- "1. Decompose & Route" --> PlannerAgent(Planner Agent);
            PlannerAgent -- "2. Returns" --> Structured_Plan{Structured Plan};

